race.comment: Lots of win chances from a few different angles. PURE HEARTED (11) has been racing at Belmont and Ascot and tested over 1800m latest there. Weakened late but the start prior was close-up in a far tougher line-up than this. Gets chance to break through. SOLASH MOON (12) has been racing here and hasn't been far away. Closed well last time to be beaten only a coupe of lengths and right in this on that run. ZADOWS LANDING (1) is an interesting runner prepared by SA trainer David Page. Has good form around the SA provincials for this level and off the inside should go close on best figures. WRITTEN SIN (9) was solid two back over 1200m then stepped quickly to a mile last time but had no luck, dragged back in tiring traffic when the winner was going forward. Well worth another chance. QUAGMIRE (2) is mixing form but placed only try at the trip and looks well placed with the claim.
